A weathered pair of hands shaping raw clay on a potter's wheel, captured in Studio Ghibli animation style with soft watercolor textures and warm amber lighting. The hands are covered in wet clay, fingers pressing deliberately into the spinning form as delicate wisps of clay spiral off. In the background, a cozy workshop filled with handmade ceramic vessels in various stages of completion sits on wooden shelves, some cracked or imperfect, others beautifully finished. Dust motes float in golden afternoon sunlight streaming through a foggy window. The scene emphasizes patience, imperfection embraced, and the quiet dignity of learning through practice. Gentle earth tones of terracotta, cream, and sage green dominate the palette.
